---------------------------
|  Watershed Segmentation |
---------------------------

These applications use fltk and VTK.
They work best if the source data is in the Meta Image format.

Segmentation can be done in 3 steps:
   1) First, smooth your data in a preprocessing step (see below).
   2) Next, run the Watershed Segmentation application (see below).
   3) Last, manipulate your segmented output to produce labeled volumes (see below).


Preprocessor Step
------------------
Run the AnisotropicDiffusionFltkGui2D or AnisotropicDiffusionFltkGui3D depending
on the dimension of your data.  



Watershed Segmentation
----------------------
Run the WatershedSegmentationFltkGui.  This is for 3 dimensional data.



Editor
------
Use the EditorFltkGui to manipulate the output from the watershed application
to prodcue a labeled volume.  

